      "abstract": "The CATS is a 15-item self-report measure designed to screen children and adolescents for trauma exposure and symptoms of PTSD. Items assess exposure to different types of trauma and emotional reactions. It is brief, sensitive, and useful for identifying youth needing further assessment.",
      "time_periods": [
        {
          "start": "2000",
          "end": "2024-12-31"
        }
      ],
      "coll_dates": [
        {
